SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 799
By Southerland
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Bishop Merriweather
of Greeneville High School on being named to
the TSWA Class 4A All-State football team.
WHEREAS, we are pleased to recognize and commend those successful high school
athletes who, through their magnificent exploits, bring honor to Tennessee and serve as
exceptional ambassadors of this State; and
WHEREAS, one such estimable individual is Bishop Merriweather of Greeneville High
School, an athlete of extraordinary talent, skill, and dedication, who has proven himself a
formidable competitor on the football field; and
WHEREAS, the Tennessee Sports Writers Association (TSWA) recently named Bishop
Merriweather to the 2025 Class 4A All-State football team as an offensive lineman in recognition
of his excellence on the gridiron for Greeneville High School; and
WHEREAS, Bishop Merriweather was also honored this season as Region 1-4A
Offensive Lineman of the Year; and
WHEREAS, Bishop Merriweather epitomizes all that is good in today's student athlete,
as he has achieved a high level of success in sports while evincing great character both on and
off the field; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Merriweather's notable achievement is a source of great pride for his
family, his community, and his school, and it is appropriate that we recognize this accomplished
athlete; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate Bishop Merriweather of
